# shadcn (local CLI — no MCP)

The shadcn MCP server is blocked by team admin. Do not rely on shadcn MCP tools.

Use the local CLI from `desktop/` instead:

```bash
npm run shadcn -- <command>
```

Common commands:

- `npm run shadcn -- info --json` — project context (components, aliases, paths)
- `npm run shadcn -- search @shadcn -q "<query>"` — find registry items
- `npm run shadcn -- docs <component>` — get docs/example URLs
- `npm run shadcn -- add <component>` — install or update a component
- `npm run shadcn -- add --dry-run <component>` — preview changes before applying
- `npm run shadcn -- view @shadcn/<item>` — inspect registry item details

Rules:

- Run all shadcn commands with `working_directory` set to `desktop/`.
- On PowerShell, quote registry namespaces: `"@shadcn"`.
- Prefer existing installed components in `src/components/ui/` before adding new ones.
- Follow shadcn critical rules: semantic colors, `Field`/`FieldGroup` for forms, `data-icon` on button icons, no `space-y-*`.
